Name.BusinessNameLine1: Big Brothers Big Sisters of Central Ohio Inc

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: Our mission is to serve the community by providing quality mentoring relationships to children & youth primiarly from single-parent homes, to offer a summer camping experience to these & other under-privileged children and to train adults to mentor Central Ohio children.
IRS990.MissionDescription: our mission is to serve the community by providing quality mentoring relationships to children & youth primarily from single-parent homes, to offer a summer camping experience to these & other under-priviledged children and to train adults to mentor central ohio children.
IRS990.Description: Mentoring: Provides mentoring to at-risk children in our community & Central Ohio schools. developing quality mentoring relationships inspiring youth to be confident, competent and caring individuals in our community.

Activity2.Description: Camp: Provides a summer camping experience to at-risk and underprivileged children from the community. Also makes camp available during the off season to campers from school, church & other outside groups. AT CAMP OTY'OKWA, CHILDREN HAVE SO MUCH FUN THEY LEARN CRITICAL LIFE SKILLS WITHOUT EVEN KNOWING IT'S HAPPENENING.

Activity3.Description: The Mentoring Center: The mentoring center trains mentees & professionalS, focusing on the whole child. Since its inception, it has trained over 9,000 people in mentoring skills & recruited over 3,300 people to become volunteers.

Form990ScheduleCPartIV.Explanation: the organization hires a lobbyist to enhance its mission and primary exempt purpose.

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.ReturnReference: Explanation of Changes to Conservation Easements:
Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: The organization holds one easement in one state (ohio) which is slightly more than 160 acres with the ohio department of natural resources. the easement is a conservation easement for the protection of a plant located on the land owned by the organization. minimal staff hours and expenses were incurred during the year to monitor/enforce the easement during the tax year.

Form990ScheduleJPartIII.Explanation: the organization provides the annual dues for the ceo's membership into the young professionals organization.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The form 990 is reviewed by the ceo and vp of finance and is provided to the board by email prior to its filing with the irs.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: officers and members of the board are required to annually sign the conflict of interest policy.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The organization annually compares salary ranges with the Big brothers big sisters of americal for all positions. the ceo's compensation is approved by the executive committee of the board. the remaining officers and key employees' salaries are determined by the ceo, which is approved by the executive committee through a salary review annually.
